ISSUED AT 1800 SATURDAY 30 NOVEMBER 2013
METEOROLOGICAL SITUATION AT 1500: AN ANTICYCLONE OF 1040 HPA CENTERED C.
370 NM WEST - SOUTHWEST OF VALENTIA IS MOVING STEADILY EASTWARDS AS A LIGHT
TO MODERATE NORTHWEST AIRFLOW COVERS THE AREA. A WEAK WARM FRONT EMBEDDED
IN THE FLOW TRACKS SOUTHEASTWARDS.
FORECAST FOR COASTS FROM SLYNE HEAD TO MALIN HEAD TO HOWTH HEAD AND FOR
THE NORTH IRISH SEA:
WIND: MAINLY NORTHWEST FORCE 3 OR 4 DECREASING FORCE 2 OR 3 LATER TONIGHT
AND BECOMING VARIABLE FORCE 2 OR 3 DURING SUNDAY MORNING.
WEATHER: SOME PATCHES OF DRIZZLE AT TIMES BUT MAINLY FAIR.
VISIBILITY: MODERATE IN ANY DRIZZLE GOOD OTHERWISE.
FORECAST FOR COASTS FROM HOWTH HEAD TO ROCHE'S POINT TO SLYNE HEAD AND
FOR THE SOUTH IRISH SEA:
WIND: NORTHWEST TO NORTH FORCE 2 OR 3. BECOMING VARIABLE FORCE 2 OR LESS
LATER TONIGHT AND IN THE MORNING.
WEATHER: MAINLY FAIR
VISIBILITY: MOSTLY GOOD.
OUTLOOK FOR A FURTHER 24 HOURS UNTIL 1800 MONDAY 02 DECEMBER 2013: LIGHT
VARIABLE WINDS BACKING SOUTHERLY LATER SUNDAY NIGHT AND BECOMING LIGHT TO
MODERATE. INCREASING MODERATE TO FRESH ON MONDAY MORNING AND BECOMING STRONG
ON NORTHWEST COASTS LATER. MAINLY FAIR WEATHER BUT SOME LOCAL PATCHES OF
MIST AND DRIZZLE.
